### [src/routes/Home.js](file:///d:/BB/news/src/routes/Home.js) — Home Page
```js
const QUICK_TAGS = ['news', 'technology', 'ai', 'business', 'construction', 'finance']
// const array at module level = defined ONCE, never re-created on render

const SORT_LABELS = {
  latest: 'Latest first',
  oldest: 'Oldest first',
  relevance: 'Most relevant'
}
// Object lookup is O(1) — faster and cleaner than if/else chains
```

```js
{QUICK_TAGS.map(function(tag) {
  return (
    <Chip
      key={tag}           // React needs a unique key for list items
      label={tag}
      color={searchTerm === tag ? 'primary' : 'default'}
      // If this tag IS the current search, color it primary (blue/highlighted)
      onClick={function() { onTagSelect(tag) }}
    />
  )
})}
```
**`key` prop:** React uses this internally to track which list items changed. Without `key`, React re-renders ALL items even when only one changes. The `key` must be unique among siblings.

