### [src/components/AppBarSearch.js](file:///d:/BB/news/src/components/AppBarSearch.js) — Top Navigation Bar

```js
const [value, setValue] = React.useState('')
// Local state: the input's current text (unrelated to global searchTerm)

const timeoutRef = React.useRef(null)
// Stores the setTimeout ID so we can cancel it

function handleChange(e) {
  const nextValue = e.target.value  // e = Event object. e.target = the input element
  setValue(nextValue)               // Update the input display immediately

  if (timeoutRef.current) clearTimeout(timeoutRef.current)  // Cancel previous timer
  
  timeoutRef.current = setTimeout(() => {
    onSearch(nextValue)   // Call parent's handler AFTER 350ms of no typing
  }, 350)
}
```

**This is called a "debounce" pattern.** Without it, every keystroke would fire an API call. With debounce, you wait for the user to stop typing for 350ms before searching. This drastically reduces API calls.

```js
React.useEffect(() => {
  return () => {
    if (timeoutRef.current) clearTimeout(timeoutRef.current)
  }
}, [])
// Empty dependency array [] = runs ONCE on mount, cleans up on unmount
// This prevents memory leaks if the component is removed while a timer is pending
```

