### [src/components/FiltersDrawer.js](file:///d:/BB/news/src/components/FiltersDrawer.js) — Sidebar Filter Panel
```js
<Drawer anchor='right' open={open} onClose={onClose}>
```
- `anchor='right'` = slides in from the right side
- `open={open}` = controlled by parent's `filtersOpen` state
- `onClose={onClose}` = called when user clicks backdrop or presses Escape

```js
<RadioGroup value={sortBy} onChange={handleSortChange}>
  <FormControlLabel value='latest' control={<Radio />} label='Latest first' />
  <FormControlLabel value='oldest' control={<Radio />} label='Oldest first' />
  <FormControlLabel value='relevance' control={<Radio />} label='Most relevant' />
</RadioGroup>
```
A **controlled component** — `value={sortBy}` means the selected radio button is always what `sortBy` says. The user's click fires `onChange`, which calls `onChangeSortBy`, which updates state in [App.js](file:///d:/BB/news/src/App.js), which flows back down as a new `sortBy` prop.

