### [src/components/ArticleCard.js](file:///d:/BB/news/src/components/ArticleCard.js) — News Card
```js
const featured = Boolean(props.featured)
// Boolean() converts any truthy/falsy value to true/false explicitly
// props.featured = index === 0 (true for first card, false for rest)
```

```js
function openDetails() {
  navigate(`/article/${article.id}`, { state: article })
  // Pass the full article object as navigation state
  // ArticleDetails.js reads this to show content INSTANTLY
}

function handleKeyDown(event) {
  if (event.key === 'Enter' || event.key === ' ') {
    event.preventDefault()  // Prevent page scroll on Space
    openDetails()
  }
}
// Makes the card keyboard-accessible (role='button' + tabIndex={0} + onKeyDown)
```

```js
function handleReadOriginalClick(event) {
  event.stopPropagation()
  // Without this: clicking "Read original" button would ALSO trigger openDetails()
  // stopPropagation() prevents the event from bubbling up to the Card's onClick
}
```

**Event Bubbling:** Click events travel UP the DOM tree. Card → Box → Article card's onClick would all fire. `stopPropagation()` stops the event at the button.

```js
<Typography
  sx={{
    overflow: 'hidden',
    display: '-webkit-box',
    WebkitBoxOrient: 'vertical',
    WebkitLineClamp: featured ? 2 : 1  // Show 2 lines on featured, 1 on others
  }}
>
```
**CSS line clamping** — limits text to N lines and shows `...`. A CSS trick using flexbox internals.

