### [src/routes/ArticleDetails.js](file:///d:/BB/news/src/routes/ArticleDetails.js) — Article Detail Page
```js
const { id } = useParams()
// Destructuring: same as: const id = useParams().id

const location = useLocation()

const [article, setArticle] = useState(location.state || null)
// If navigated from a card → location.state has the article data
// If URL is typed directly → location.state is null, article is null
```

**Two-source strategy:**
1. If user clicked a card → article data is instantly available from `location.state`
2. In BOTH cases, the API call runs to get fresh/complete data
3. If API fails but `location.state` exists, the cached data still shows

```js
if (loading && !article) {
  return <CircularProgress />  // Spinner: loading AND no cached data
}
if (!article) {
  return <Typography>Article not found</Typography>  // No data at all
}
// If article exists (from cache): show it immediately, no spinner
```

