## 6. Complete Data Flow

```
User types 'ai' in search bar
        ↓
AppBarSearch.handleChange() fires
Debounce waits 350ms
        ↓
onSearch('ai') called → App.js setSearchTerm('ai')
        ↓
React re-renders: searchTerm='ai' flows to AppRoutes → Home → NewsList
        ↓
NewsList Effect 1: query changed → setItems([]), setPage(0)
        ↓
NewsList Effect 2: page=0 changed → loadNews() called
        ↓
newsService.search('ai', 0, {sortBy:'latest'})
        ↓
buildUrl('/search_by_date', {query:'ai', tags:'story', page:0, hitsPerPage:12})
        ↓
fetch('https://hn.algolia.com/api/v1/search_by_date?query=ai&tags=story&page=0&hitsPerPage=12')
        ↓
JSON response → data.hits.map(mapHitToArticle)
Each hit: cleanText() → getTagFromText() → getTagThumbnail()
        ↓
setItems([...12 articles]), setHasMore(true)
React re-renders → Grid of ArticleCards displayed
        ↓
User scrolls down
IntersectionObserver fires
setPage(1)
        ↓
Effect 2 runs again with page=1
Fetches next 12 articles
setItems([...previous + 12 new, deduplicated, sorted])
```

