## 7. Viva Q&A — Best Answers

**Q: Why React instead of plain HTML/JS?**  
React manages UI updates automatically. When state changes, React figures out which parts of the DOM need updating (via virtual DOM diffing). In plain JS you'd have to manually `document.getElementById().innerHTML = ...` everywhere.

**Q: Why Vite instead of Create React App?**  
Vite uses native ES modules and esbuild. Dev server starts in <300ms vs CRA's 5-10 seconds. Hot Module Replacement (HMR) is near-instant. CRA is deprecated as of 2023.

**Q: Why MUI instead of writing custom CSS?**  
MUI provides accessible, consistent, responsive components. Accessibility (ARIA, keyboard navigation) is built-in. Theming (dark/light) is one line of code. Building a Button with ripple, hover states, focus rings from scratch takes hours.

**Q: Why the Algolia Hacker News API?**  
Free, no API key, no rate limiting (within reason), real news data, supports search and pagination out of the box.

**Q: Why no Redux / Zustand?**  
The app's state is simple: 4 values in [App.js](file:///d:/BB/news/src/App.js). Redux adds boilerplate (actions, reducers, store) that isn't justified until state becomes complex or needs to be shared across many deeply nested components.

**Q: What is a "controlled component"?**  
A form element whose value is controlled by React state, not the DOM. The input's `value` comes from state, and `onChange` updates that state. React is always the single source of truth.

**Q: What is a "pure function"?**  
A function that: (1) given the same inputs, always returns the same output, (2) has no side effects (doesn't modify external state). [cleanText()](file:///d:/BB/news/src/services/newsService.js#50-64), [buildUrl()](file:///d:/BB/news/src/services/newsService.js#15-28), [formatDate()](file:///d:/BB/news/src/utils/date.js#1-13), [uniqueById()](file:///d:/BB/news/src/features/news/NewsList.js#27-35) are all pure functions.

**Q: How does infinite scroll work here?**  
A tiny `<div>` (`loadMoreRef`) sits at the bottom of the article list. `IntersectionObserver` watches it. When it enters the viewport (or 500px before), we increment `page`. The page change triggers the fetch `useEffect`, which loads the next batch and appends it.

**Q: What is event propagation / bubbling?**  
When you click a button inside a card, the click event fires on the button, then bubbles up to the card, then the document. `stopPropagation()` breaks the bubble chain, preventing parent click handlers from firing.

**Q: What is the `useRef` hook for?**  
Two uses: (1) Access a DOM element directly without re-rendering (e.g., `loadMoreRef`). (2) Store a mutable value that survives renders but doesn't cause re-renders when changed (e.g., `timeoutRef` for debounce).

**Q: Why `useMemo` for the theme?**  
`createTheme()` is an expensive computation (builds a large object with colors, breakpoints, spacing etc.). Without `useMemo`, it would run on EVERY render. With `useMemo([mode])`, it only runs when `mode` changes — which is rare.
